About my Data

  • Amazon Reviews in US for Musical Instruments.
  • Since, it was a .tsv file, I converted it to .csv file first and then imported it in a pandas dataframe in Python for analysis.
  • Finally, my dataframe had the following attributes: -Used drop.na function in python to drop some rows having missing values.

Star Ratings

  • I segregated music products according to their star ratings and got the following results:

  • So, out of 904705, 731398 people gave it a 4 and 5 star rating which tells that over 83% reviews are positive.

Positive and Negative Reviews

  • I considered star rating 3 as a neutral review and removed all the neutrally rated products.
  • I then divided the products into positively and negatively rated products with 3 as the threshold.

Most used positive and negative words

  • I then used the countVectoriser and transformed the data into a document term matrix and then extracted the feature names into a numpy array.
  • After sorting, I found out the 10 most used words in negative and positive reviews.
